<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{3}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}-{7}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.123</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{3}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}-{7}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{-{3}{x}}}=-\frac{{7}}{{3}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{7}}{{3}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{7}}{{3}}\right)}}}}{{-{{3}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx-{0.123}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

